<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet href="\\Ameras0036\Data\BIEM_PRODUCTION_AMERICA\053_NJT\Application\p-xml\XSL\053_NJT_ib.xslt" type="text/xsl"?><!--thru 053_NJT_p-iem_IB.xslt--><ib miid="BOM00775" doc-type="MI" maint-item-desc="Information Signs" doc-name="BOM00775_MI" doc-title="Information Signs" lock-counter="30" search-index="mim-sys9-dno" show-e-list="yes" e-list-number="09 03" giid-maint-item-desc="Information Signs" id-document="4501" id-document-version="41249" doc-version="7" pmt-version="14" gmt-version="12" user-defined-1="" user-defined-2="" user-defined-3="" oem-part-no="" device-name=""><maintenance-item><para reuse="all">Three types of information signs are installed
in the NJ Transit multi-level cars:</para><list type="bulleted" reuse="all"><list-item><para reuse="all">Front
Destination Signs (FDS) </para></list-item><list-item><para reuse="all">Side Destination Sign (SDS) </para></list-item><list-item><para reuse="all">Interior Message Signs (IMS). </para></list-item></list><para reuse="all">All signs are an assembly made of monochrome
LCD character tiles arranged in a single row. Each LCD backlight
is made of yellow LED, meaning that all letters displayed are to
be monochrome yellow color. All displays are protected with a glazing
window made of fireproof polycarbonate used to protect the LCD and
to minimize reflection of external lights.</para><para reuse="all">The information signs are distributed by type
throughout the NJ Transit multi-level cars. (See Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="BABFCJFB"></iref></ref-container>.) </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="BABFCJFB">Information Sign Locations</title><tgroup cols="8" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.500in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.688in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="0.688in"></colspec><colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.688in"></colspec><colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="2.063in"></colspec><colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="8" colname="8" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" valign="middle">SIGN TYPE</entry><entry colname="2" morerows="1" valign="middle">ID</entry><entry namest="3" nameend="4">CHARACTERS</entry><entry colname="5" morerows="1" valign="middle">LOCATION</entry><entry namest="6" nameend="8">QTY/CAR</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="3">QTY</entry><entry colname="4">HEIGHT</entry><entry colname="6">C</entry><entry colname="7">S</entry><entry colname="8">T</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">Front Destination Sign</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">FDS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">8</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">3 in.</entry><entry colname="5">F-end vestibule</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">-</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1">Side Destination Sign</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">SDS1</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">15</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">3 in.</entry><entry colname="5">A-end and F-end, upper level, left side</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">SDS2</entry><entry colname="3"></entry><entry colname="4"></entry><entry colname="5">B-end, upper level, right side</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="5">Interior Message Sign</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS1</entry><entry colname="3" morerows="5" align="center">15</entry><entry colname="4" morerows="5" align="center">2 in.</entry><entry colname="5">A-end and F-end, quarter point vestibule</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS2</entry><entry colname="5">A-end and F-end, lower level, left side</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS3</entry><entry colname="5">B-end, lower-level, right side</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS4</entry><entry colname="5">B-end, quarter point vestibule</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS5</entry><entry colname="5">A-end and F-end, upper-level</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="2" align="center">IMS6</entry><entry colname="5">B-end, upper-level</entry><entry colname="6" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="7" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="8" align="center">1</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">Each sign on a car is assigned a unique ID.
Consequently, signs can be addressed and controlled individually
or as subgroups through the Data Car Network by the Communication
Control Unit (CCU). </para><para reuse="all">All signs have a touchpad assembly with the
following pushbutton and indicators. (See Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="BABJAFDF"></iref></ref-container>.) </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="BABJAFDF">Information Signs Pushbuttons and Indicators</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.750in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">LABEL</entry><entry colname="2">TYPE</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">SER</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Pushbutton</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Service Pin<para reuse="all">Pressing
the pushbutton sends a service pin message over the DCN.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">SER</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Yellow LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Service Pin Indicator<para reuse="all">On steady (yellow) or blinking (yellow) indicates
that the sign is not configured or has failed.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">RX</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Green LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Reception Indicator<para reuse="all">Blinking (green) indicates that the sign is receiving
data from the DCN.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="left">TX</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Green LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Transmission indicator<para reuse="all">Blinking (green) indicates that the sign is transmitting
data to the DCN.</para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></maintenance-item></ib>